data.chText: 嬉皮士（拒绝西方生活方式的人，常留长发、衣着鲜艳、吸毒。嬉皮士运动在20世纪60年代最盛行）
data.enText: a person who rejects the way that most people live in Western society, often having long hair, wearing brightly coloured clothes and taking illegal drugs. The hippie movement was most popular in the 1960s.

word_means: 嬉皮士(拒绝西方生活方式的人，常留长发、衣着鲜艳、吸毒。嬉皮士运动在20世纪60年代最盛行)

means: 嬉皮士(拒绝西方生活方式的人，常留长发、衣着鲜艳、吸毒。嬉皮士运动在20世纪60年代最盛行)

tr: someone who rejects the established culture
advocates extreme liberalism in politics and lifestyle

value.def: Hippies were young people in the 1960s and 1970s who rejected conventional ways of living, dressing, and behaving, and tried to live a life based on peace and love. Hippies often had long hair and many took drugs.
value.tran: 嬉皮士（20世纪60、70年代的青年颓废派，摈弃传统的生活、着装和行为方式，提倡和平与友爱，常蓄长发并吸毒）
